[MK] case called at 2:02pm 
Defendant Keanu W Moss appears via videoconferencing from the Jefferson County Jail, in custody, along with Public Defender Amber Rumpf (the PD appears for bond-purposes only; Mr. Moss does not qualify for PD representation).  ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin. 
The Court finds that the video-connection is sight and sound sufficient. 

Attorney Rumpf verifies that the address listed on the Criminal Complaint is correct. 
Service of Complaint admitted, reading waived, the charges and maximum penalties are recited.
Right to counsel is given.  Mr. Moss indicates that he would like information on petitioning the Court for the appointment of counsel. 
The Court adjourns the Initial Appearance, tolling the preliminary hearing time limit. The Court preserves all Constitutional and jurisdictional objections 
During arguments on bond Victim 1, who is present in the courtroom, makes a statement requesting contact. 

The Court requires a $2,500 Signature Bond with conditions:
--not to make any acts or threats of violence
--to maintain absolute sobriety 
--no discussion of the facts of the case with M.M. as referred to in the Victim Witness Key and the Criminal Complaint 
recess 2:11pm.
 
NEXT: Adjourned Initial Appearance (and status-of-counsel hearing) on April 22nd at 1:15pm.
